review_blob:
This is,overall,a very good wheat beer.Aroma & appearance are very high,but the taste,although good,falls a little below the top 2 mentioned categories.
Appearance is somewhere between a wheat beer and a dark wheat beer.I should drink this more often!

This is very good;I guess this Kellerweizen shows why after so many years I keep trying new beers,I get beautiful surprises like this.
Will definitely keep an eye out for this style in the future.Only negative,it finishes a little watery.

Beer looks great for the first minute,not so much after that.The beer is a too tart for my liking,and "disturbs" the other flavors...which of course will lower my palate score.
Thought it was going to be better.
Citrus,hoppy,crisp tasting beer that finishes very refreshing.I might have had a better Japanese brewed pils over the years,but offhand I cannot think of one.

A creamy,chocolaty,fruity,dunkelweizen. Definitely not your standard dunkelweizen and would probably only buy this again when I wanted something different from the ordinary.
Not bad.

Everything is below average and on the whole it is difficult to not write a complete mess.
15 second head,much under carbonated,north american wheat beer flavor.As boring to write about as it is to drink.
I have easily had this over 300 times!(that is also my review).

15 second lasting head.Roasted malts and soft dark chocolate.
Average porter

This beer scared me;I love dunkelweizen beer,in fact it is my favorite style.I have had dunkelweizen beers and was still thinking about the taste 4-5 days later.I have had dreams about how happy I was when drinking dunkelweizen beers.I have bought plane tickets,partly,to drink dunkelweizen.
If this would of been my first dunkelweizen all of the above might never have happened.If this was my first dunkelweizen,I might not have ever had a second.
The worst of any Beaus that I have drunk,and drain poured the last 33% of the bottle.

Going for the Brasseurs RJ wheat beer trifecta,I "cashed" on both the hefe and the dunkel and am now going for the Weizen Bock.
Although I like it(maybe a bit to sweet),I believe that my ticket was a winner;i might not like it as much as the other two,but i generally like my beers under 5.5 rather then over 7.

Could use a little more banana flavor,could do with a lighter hand on the spices.
On tap at the brewpub.
Good.All aromas,tastes and palate can be described by using soft,mellow or light,but with this beer that is not a bad thing.

I would put the palate at 3.5 and the taste at 7.5.
Legit dunkelweizen that is on par with their hefeweizen.

Munichesque.One of the better Helles that I have had for a while.
Tasty dark malts.On tap at the brewpub.
Have not had a cigarette since 1980.Have not thought-seriously-about having a cigarette since 1985.That all changed today...
beer_name: Pit-Caribou Ltoile du Brasseur Stout  lAvoine

review_blob:
Looks like a dunkelweizen,not sure that it tastes like one though(certainly not one brewed in Germany).
It not that it was not good,in fact it was quite refreshing,but just not like anyone of the 100(+) traditional dunkleweizens that i have had.
Very malty in taste,not much to the aroma.Much better pils on offer at this price point to be bought in Montreal.
I would describe all aspects of this wit as subtle,just not sure if that is a good thing or not.At the end I decided that I would like to drink the beer again ,so I graded subtle as positive.
beer_name: Le Trou du Diable Blanche de Shawi

review_blob:
More then 1 type of chocolate,cigarette/ash in a creamy dry stout.
Left the beer-1/2 way through- to answer the door(which took about 5 minute).The beer tasted "better" after being in the air for a bit- seemed to wake up.

Too sweet and not enough body to be enjoyed.
A macro in craft clothing;id have to be really thirsty on a very hot day to want this again.

Toss a handful of candied fruit in your mouth then wash it down with a chocolate coffee-voila,that is what this beer tastes like to me.
On tap at brouhaha.
beer_name: Le Trou du Diable Baron Noir

review_blob:
Just so slightly above what a "good" amber lager tastes like.
-this comprises all that need to be said about the beer;sometimes 75 characters is way too much!

"Its funny",I only bought this because I am too jet-lagged to get to a store that sells craft beer,and I had oatmeal for the first time in 35 years-2 days ago.
This is good,with a true/meaty oatmeal taste.

I like a restaurant that makes a few dishes from one region,& I like a brewery that makes no more then 10 different beers.
Nice rich malty lager that is refreshing.
A good porter,nothing more and nothing less.So similar to so many other porters,no need to get into specifics.

First beer that I ever "put away" for a while.Do not usually drink/like beers over 5.9%,but I did like this.
Aroma & taste mostly chocolate and coffee.
Creamy,smooth,Works well this time of the year and for around valentines day.

Very Good!
Aroma-mostly coffee & chocolate,Taste-mostly chocolate(s),nut,& caramel.
I was told by friends to pick this up if I ever saw it on the shelves;this time my friends were right.
Smooth & mellow does not work for me with jazz but it does work for me with this stout.Black in color,nicely sweet,roasted malts and creamy chocolate.
Maybe the worst wheat beer that I ever had.One of the reasons that I like wheat beers is the aftertaste;the aftertaste of this made me go for a bottle of pop.

This beer left me with more questions then answers;it tastes like a regular wheat beer with a spice added,but i do not know what the spice is.
It has a slightly higher alcohol content, but drinks like it has a slightly lower alcohol content.
Since my wheat beer drinking is not weather affected,i would prefer a regular wheat beer during the holidays.
On draught at the brewpub;banana,tart,fruit,thirst quenching! Bought a few bottles home from the brewery that were bottled 1 day earlier.

bought in H.K.(aeon) for bday and holiday festivities at home;aroma is chocolate,wheat,banana.taste is of light chocolate,wheat,malt.can drink this all day no matter what the season/temperature outside.very,very,very good!
bought in H.K(citysuper,tst)for bday & holiday festivities at home;just a little more then your middle of the road german hefeweizen.nicely banana sweet with a little spice at the end.

a light/creamy smoked porter.
might not be "as smoked" as what you would get in Bamberg,but i have no complaints.
"stolen" from my buddy s fridge;i think if this was called simple golden ale,very few people would complain.i came to my friends place-i took this from the fridge-i was thirsty-job done!
nice dubbel.chocolate,malts,liquorice,a touch hoppy.at the right time i could have a few of these.
i like this,probably most because it is a chance to have a good dunkel weizen that is different from what is made in germany.some malt,some banana,in a sweet donker.

comments were for on tap at the brewpub;nice refreshing beer especially after a walk-around haarlem day.taste was lighter and watered down compared to the bottle.
glad to try a dutch dunkel weizen but it does not compare to what i have drunk from germany!

(funny)never heard of this bier & it took a paris bottle shop for me to notice.
all the standard flavors are here but add other fruits to the usually only banana flavor...maybe making it a type of dessert weissbier!

(f.u guinness)in the early 1990s,i got the chance to bum around brittany for a couple of years.Once found,initially in a tourist shop,it was my special beer for 2 years.
i like this a lot,it is a well made beer.do you like buckwheat soup,buckwheat noodles(soba) &/or buckwheat bread...i would guess that you might like this.
do not usually like this type pf beer (ale),but i like this!looks good,smells good(perfumie)and goes well with seafood.
it looks great,it tastes good,but it is just too light bodied to score any higher then i did.

ready others comments,i guess that this is a bitter pils;never liked a bitter bier before and i did not find this bier bitter either.oh well,maybe next time i will choose another "bitter" pils and compare!

really nice light mouth feel to this kellerbier;i think that is one of the bier things i am learning on this trip to germany...i like the taste of their biers,but its tasty lingering sensations in my mouth is where i am really getting "off".
the palate on this hefeweizen is maybe in my top 5(very rich with flavor that stays on your tongue for a while)but i get a medicine type flavor at the end that just did not go down well.
this hefeweizen reminds me of the story of goldilocks;some hehes are too sweet,some are too bland,but this one is just right.
palate is 3.5 which gives an overall score of 13.5.   caramel.banana,chocolate,bubblegum and spices.  very good,very refreshing.thank you bavarian purity law of 1516!
brown color,aroma/taste of malt,caramel & bananas.like it,but do not love it.
roasted malts,chocolate,something fruit,blah-blah-blah/do they make a stout in london that i can give a 14/20 score!?
this is one of the nicest (looking)beers to pour with equally nice lacing.that is everything positive i can say.
